I’ve got a new local lead: Foundry’s RPC cache stores full account bytecode and storage snapshots. I’m scanning those cached accounts for ERC404-like contracts now, because if the Rugged token was touched in any nearby cached run I can recover its address entirely offline and harden the verifier around it.
